  <h3>Remaining Season Heat in {{ state.name }} (Base 50 GDD)</h3>

  <p class="small" style="margin-top:-0.25rem;">
    <a href="/guides/how-frost-dates-and-growing-degree-days-work-together/">Growing Degree Days</a> (Base 50°F) measure heat accumulation.
    “Remaining GDD” shows how much usable heat is typically still available from a given date onward in a normal season.
  </p>

  {% set preferredDates = ["05-15", "06-01", "07-01", "08-01"] %}
  {% set filteredRows = [] %}

  {% for row in state.gdd_remaining %}
    {% if row.date in preferredDates %}
      {% set filteredRows = filteredRows.concat([row]) %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}

  {% set rows = filteredRows if filteredRows.length else state.gdd_remaining %}

  <div class="tableWrap">
    <table class="table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Planting date</th>
          <th>Base</th>
          <th>Typical GDD still available</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {% for row in rows %}
          <tr>
            <td>{{ row.date | mmddLong }}</td>
            <td>{{ row.base }}</td>
            <td>{% if row.gdd != null %}{{ row.gdd }}{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
          </tr>
        {% endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:0.75rem;">
    Use these values to judge whether a crop or variety still has enough heat left after planting. This is especially helpful for later sowings, shorter-maturity choices, and deciding whether a second round is realistic.
  </p>

  {% if state.frost.status != "normal" %}
    <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
      Remaining GDD to first frost is less meaningful where there is no typical frost boundary in the normals dataset.
    </p>
  {% endif %}
